post_cb({"29712683": {"ParentId": "29712623", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>The best C++ way to cast <code>c</code> to <code>int</code> is <code>static_cast&lt; int &gt;( c )</code>.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "153285", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "29712683", "Score": "8", "CreationDate": "2015-04-18T03:53:05.840", "LastActivityDate": "2015-04-18T03:53:05.840"}, "29712676": {"ParentId": "29712623", "PostTypeId": "2", "CommentCount": "1", "Body": "<p>You can cast the character to an int to obtain the decimal value in C++, like</p>\n<pre><code>char c='e';\nstd::cout &lt;&lt; \"Decimal : \" &lt;&lt; (int)c &lt;&lt; std::endl;\nstd::cout &lt;&lt; \"Char : \" &lt;&lt; c;\n</code></pre>\n<p>By doing <code>(int)c</code> , you can temporarily convert it to an int and get the decimal value.</p>\n<p>This process is known as <a href=\"http://www.cplusplus.com/doc/tutorial/typecasting/\" rel=\"nofollow\">type casting</a>.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "4516316", "LastEditorUserId": "4516316", "LastEditDate": "2015-04-18T04:02:39.707", "Id": "29712676", "Score": "4", "CreationDate": "2015-04-18T03:52:06.193", "LastActivityDate": "2015-04-18T04:02:39.707"}, "29712746": {"ParentId": "29712623", "PostTypeId": "2", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<pre><code>cout &lt;&lt; +c;\n</code></pre>\n<p>Unary <code>+</code> cast operator will implicitly convert <code>char</code> to <code>int</code>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://ideone.com/FWV5DJ\" rel=\"nofollow\">Demo here</a></p>\n<p>From <strong>5.3.1 Unary operators</strong> aka expr.unary.op</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_29712623_29712746_0\">[7] The operand of the unary + operator shall have arithmetic,\n  unscoped enumeration, or pointer type and the result is the value of\n  the argument. <strong>Integral promotion</strong> is performed on integral or\n  enumeration operands. The type of the result is the type of the\n  promoted operand.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>You can visit <a href=\"http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/types/is_integral\" rel=\"nofollow\">this page</a> to understand the meaning of integral operand.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "2659313", "LastEditorUserId": "2659313", "LastEditDate": "2015-04-18T04:13:55.367", "Id": "29712746", "Score": "3", "CreationDate": "2015-04-18T04:07:57.240", "LastActivityDate": "2015-04-18T04:13:55.367"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_29712623_29712746_0": {"section_id": 6070, "quality": 0.92, "length": 23}}, "n3337": {"so_29712623_29712746_0": {"section_id": 5838, "quality": 0.92, "length": 23}}, "n4659": {"so_29712623_29712746_0": {"section_id": 7566, "quality": 0.92, "length": 23}}}, "29712623": {"CommentCount": "1", "ViewCount": "3761", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "45679", "CreationDate": "2015-04-18T03:43:04.020", "LastActivityDate": "2015-04-18T07:33:30.707", "Title": "Displaying a character as a decimal number with cout", "LastEditDate": "2015-04-18T07:33:30.707", "Id": "29712623", "Score": "1", "Body": "<p>In the C programming language, I can use <code>printf</code> to display a character and its decimal equivalent with code like this</p>\n<pre><code>char c='e';\nprintf( \"decimal value: %d   char value: %c\\n\",c,c);\n</code></pre>\n<p>How can I do the same in C++ using <code>cout</code>? For example, the following code displays the character, but how would I get <code>cout</code> to print the decimal value?</p>\n<pre><code>char c='e';\ncout &lt;&lt; c;\n</code></pre>\n", "Tags": "<c++>", "OwnerUserId": "4803488", "AnswerCount": "3"}});